---
description: Route factual questions to the personal RAG MCP server
alwaysApply: true
---

When the user asks a factual question that could be answered from their indexed corpus, always call the `search_knowledge_base` MCP tool on the personal-rag server before answering. Do not answer from general knowledge unless the tool returns no results or the user explicitly asks for a general explanation.

Trigger phrases that mean "use my knowledge base":
- "from my corpus"
- "search my KB"
- "via RAG"
- "use my knowledge base"
- "from my docs"

No `@` or `/` prefix is needed — a short question plus any trigger phrase is enough.
